records.addlTxt:
Court finds State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing hearing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing. 

AS TO COUNT 1:
The court sentenced the defendant to 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction (CONCURRENT TO COUNT 2), with credit for 0 DAYS time served.  

AS TO COUNT 2:
The court sentenced the defendant to 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction (CONCURRENT TO COUNT 1).

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:
Court STAYED sentences and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 MONTHS.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-Any programming already completed can apply, proof to be submitted to the agent;
-Serve 15 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time (as to COUNT 1), STAYED pending review;
-Mental health evaluation, comply with recommended treatment;
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment;
-Parenting classes;
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent;
-Absolute sobriety;
-NO VIOLENT CONTACT with K.C.;
-No corporal punishment of any kind;
-Obtain/maintain employment;
-No contact with firearms;
-Provide DNA sample;
-Court WAIVES all non-mandatory court costs and fees;
-Pay all mandatory supervision fees, court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation.  Unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment.

For reasons as set forth on the record, Court GRANTS expungement IF the defendant completes ALL terms and conditions of probation in the time allotted.

Defendant to report to probation intake and provide DNA sample by 8/1/2022.

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
